This paper deals with reachability games in the context of Dynamic Epistemic Logic (DEL), which is a logical framework for reasoning about knowledge and belief in multi-agent systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves the study of strategy existence and decision-making, which are typical topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Game theory (cs.GT) is also relevant since the paper deals with games and strategies. The paper also involves decision-making in a distributed setting, which is related to Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper involves some results on decidability, which is related to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
